![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/2bcca300-2777-4a7b-979b-ed08148f8517/processed_16837.jpg)

New claims from industry scooper Daniel RPK suggest that principal photography for the highly anticipated Avengers: Doomsday is concluding this week, with significant and potentially world-breaking plot details emerging alongside the production update. According to the reports, the film will see Doctor Doom harboring a "vendetta against the Multiverse" and will feature a startling storyline where the X-Men's universe is cursed to annihilate other realities, including the MCU's primary Earth-616.

The production rumor indicates that while initial filming is wrapping up, reshoots are already planned for a later date to accommodate a script that is reportedly still being refined. This aligns with previous whispers of a fluid and ambitious creative process for the multiverse-spanning epic.

The alleged plot points offer the most detailed glimpse yet into the narrative of the forthcoming film. The idea of Doctor Doom targeting the entire multiverse suggests a villain whose scale of ambition may eclipse even that of Thanos. While the specifics of his "vendetta" remain unclear, it positions him as a cosmic-level threat from his very introduction.

Perhaps the most dramatic of the rumored details is the plot involving the X-Men. The concept of their universe being "cursed to destroy other universes" introduces a tragic and compelling conflict, forcing the beloved mutant team into an antagonistic role against their will. This narrative framework would provide a powerful explanation for a potential clash between the Avengers and the X-Men, a showdown fans have long anticipated.

These latest rumors from Daniel RPK come on the heels of several other significant claims he has made regarding the future of the Avengers. In recent months, he has also reported that Deadpool is set to appear in both Avengers: Doomsday and its sequel, Avengers: Secret Wars. Another prominent rumor that gained traction was the reported return of Chris Evans and Hayley Atwell to filming, sparking widespread speculation about the roles their characters might play in the multiversal conflict.

While Daniel RPK has a track record that includes both notable successes and misses, these latest details paint a picture of an Avengers film aiming for a scale that could redefine the Marvel Cinematic Universe. An official synopsis for the film has confirmed that Doctor Doom, portrayed by Robert Downey Jr., will be a master of both cutting-edge science and powerful magic, set to "unleash a cascading crisis across the entire multiverse." This official description lends credence to the rumors of a multiverse-level threat, though it does not confirm the specifics of the X-Men's role or Doom's ultimate motivations. As with all unconfirmed reports, these details remain speculative until officially addressed by Marvel Studios.